  title: Cricoid Cartilage
  description: The cricoid cartilage is a ring-shaped structure located below the
    thyroid cartilage and above the trachea.The cricoid cartilage helps maintain
    an open airway and serves as an attachment point for ligaments and muscles involved
    in speech and breathing.
